[{"location":"#demographics","page":"Home","title":"demographics","text":"Documentation for demographics.\n\n","category":"section"},{"location":"#demographics.demographics","page":"Home","title":"demographics.demographics","text":"Demographics package for simulating stellar and planetary systems.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"module"},{"location":"#demographics.C0","page":"Home","title":"demographics.C0","text":"Baseline CDPP coefficient.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"constant"},{"location":"#demographics.C1","page":"Home","title":"demographics.C1","text":"First magnitude coefficient.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"constant"},{"location":"#demographics.C2","page":"Home","title":"demographics.C2","text":"Second magnitude coefficient.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"constant"},{"location":"#demographics.α","page":"Home","title":"demographics.α","text":"α coefficient for beta distributions of eccentricities\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"constant"},{"location":"#demographics.β","page":"Home","title":"demographics.β","text":"β coefficient for beta distribution of eccentricities\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"constant"},{"location":"#demographics.draw_inclination_angle-Tuple{Int64}","page":"Home","title":"demographics.draw_inclination_angle","text":"draw_inclination_angle(N) -> cosi_array\n\nArguments\n\nN::Int: Number of planets.\n\nReturns\n\ncosi_array: Array of cosine of inclination angle for the planets.\n\nDescription\n\nDraw inclination angles cosine for N planets from a uniform distribution between 0 and 1\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#demographics.draw_num_planets-Tuple{Float64}","page":"Home","title":"demographics.draw_num_planets","text":"draw_num_planets(meanN) -> num_planets::Int\n\nArguments\n\nmeanN::Float64: Mean number of planets per star.    \n\nReturns\n\nnum_planets::Int: number of actual planets for one star.\n\nDescription\n\nDraw the number of planets for one star from a Poisson distribution with mean ⟨N⟩.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#demographics.draw_orbital_eccentricity-Tuple{Int64, Float64, Float64}","page":"Home","title":"demographics.draw_orbital_eccentricity","text":"draw_orbital_eccentricity(N,α,β) -> e_array\n\nArguments\n\nN::Int: Number of planets.\nα::Float64: Alpha parameter for the Beta distribution.\nβ::Float64: Beta parameter for the Beta distribution.\n\nReturns\n\ne_array: Array of orbital eccentricities for the planets.\n\nDescription\n\nDraw orbital eccentricities for N planets from a Beta distribution with parameters α and β. Van Eylen & Albrecht 2015\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#demographics.draw_periastron_angle-Tuple{Int64}","page":"Home","title":"demographics.draw_periastron_angle","text":"draw_periastron_angle(N) -> ω_array\n\nArguments\n\nN::Int: Number of planets.\n\nReturns\n\nω_array: Array of periastron angles for the planets.\n\nDescription\n\nDraw periastron angles for N planets from a uniform distribution between -π and π\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#demographics.hr_cdpp-Tuple{Any}","page":"Home","title":"demographics.hr_cdpp","text":"hr_cdpp(T)\n\nArguments\n\nT::Float64: TESS magnitude of the star.\n\nReturns\n\nFloat64: 1-hour CDPP in ppm.\n\nDescription\n\nCalculate one hour CDPP to get detectibility metric for TESS data.\nEquation 1 from Kunimoto et al. (2022).\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#demographics.impact_parameter-Union{Tuple{T}, NTuple{5, T}} where T<:AbstractFloat","page":"Home","title":"demographics.impact_parameter","text":"impact_parameter(a,cosi,e,Rₛ,ω) -> b\n\nArguments\n\na::Float64: Semi-major axis of the planet's orbit.\ncosi::Float64: Cosine of the inclination angle.\ne::Float64: Orbital eccentricity.\nRₛ::Float64: Radius of the star.\nω::Float64: Periastron angle.\n\nReturns\n\nb::Float64: Impact parameter of the transit.\n\nDescription\n\nCalculate the impact parameter of a transiting exoplanet given its orbital parameters and the host star's radius.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#demographics.mass_ratio_sim-Tuple{Float64, Float64, Float64}","page":"Home","title":"demographics.mass_ratio_sim","text":"mass_ratio_sim(q_max::Float64, q_min::Float64, n::Float64) -> q::Float64\n\nArguments\n\nq_max::Float64: Maximum mass ratio (planet mass / star mass).\nq_min::Float64: Minimum mass ratio (planet mass / star mass).\nn::Float64: Power-law index for the mass ratio distribution.\n\nReturns\n\n<q>::Float64: Mean of planet star mass ratio.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#demographics.mean_planet_N-Tuple{Float64, Float64}","page":"Home","title":"demographics.mean_planet_N","text":"meanplanetN(β::Float64, q_mean::Float64) -> <N>::Float64\n\nArguments\n\nβ::Float64: sum of all planet mass / stellar mass.\nq_mean::Float64: Mean of planet star mass ratio.\n\nReturns\n\n<N>::Float64: Mean number of planets per star.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#demographics.orbit_seperation_sim-Tuple{Float64, Float64, Float64}","page":"Home","title":"demographics.orbit_seperation_sim","text":"orbitseperationsim(amax::Float64, amin::Float64, n::Float64) -> <a>::Float64\n\nArguments\n\na_max::Float64: Maximum orbital separation.\na_min::Float64: Minimum orbital separation.\nn::Float64: Power-law index for the orbital separation distribution.\n\nReturns\n\n<a>::Float64: Mean of orbital separation.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#demographics.random_a_sim-NTuple{4, Float64}","page":"Home","title":"demographics.random_a_sim","text":"randomasim(u::Float64, amax::Float64, amin::Float64, n::Float64) -> a::Float64\n\nArguments\n\nu::Float64: Random uniform variable between 0 and 1.\na_max::Float64: Maximum orbital separation.\na_min::Float64: Minimum orbital separation.\nn::Float64: Power-law index for the orbital separation distribution.\n\nReturns\n\na::Float64: Randomly sampled orbital separation.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#demographics.random_q_sim-NTuple{4, Float64}","page":"Home","title":"demographics.random_q_sim","text":"random_q_sim(u::Float64, q_max::Float64, q_min::Float64, n::Float64) -> q::Float64\n\nArguments\n\nu::Float64: Random uniform variable between 0 and 1.\nq_max::Float64: Maximum mass ratio (planet mass / star mass).\nq_min::Float64: Minimum mass ratio (planet mass / star mass).\nn::Float64: Power-law index for the mass ratio distribution.\n\nReturns\n\nq::Float64: Randomly sampled planet star mass ratio.\n\nDescription\n\nRandomly sampled planet star mass ratio.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#demographics.transit_SNR-Union{Tuple{T}, NTuple{6, T}} where T<:AbstractFloat","page":"Home","title":"demographics.transit_SNR","text":"transit_SNR(Rₚ,Rₛ,CDPP,T_dur,δ,Cont) -> SNR\n\nArguments\n\nRₚ::Float64: Radius of the planet.\nRₛ::Float64: Radius of the star.\nCDPP::Float64: Combined Differential Photometric Precision of the star.\nT_dur::Float64: Duration of the transit in hours.\nδ::Float64: Transit depth.\nCont::Float64: Star's contamination ratio from CTL.\n\nReturns\n\nSNR::Float64: Signal-to-noise ratio of the transit.\n\nDescription\n\nCalculate the signal-to-noise ratio (SNR) of a transit given the planet and star parameters.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#demographics.transit_duration-Union{Tuple{T}, NTuple{8, T}} where T<:AbstractFloat","page":"Home","title":"demographics.transit_duration","text":"transit_duration(a, Rₛ, Rₚ, e, ω, cosi, P) -> T_dur\n\nArguments\n\na::Float64: Semi-major axis of the planet's orbit.\nRₛ::Float64: Radius of the star.\nRₚ::Float64: Radius of the planet.\ne::Float64: Orbital eccentricity.\nω::Float64: Periastron angle.\ncosi::Float64: Cosine of the inclination angle.\nP::Float64: Orbital period of the planet.\nb::Float64: Impact parameter of the transit.\n\nReturns\n\nT_dur::Float64: Duration of the transit in hour.\n\nDescription\n\nCalculate the duration of a transit for a planet given its orbital parameters and the host star's radius\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"}]
